_online2Description:
This experiment session is a continuation of the previous session of the experiment "Letter and Reading". It requires a computer with at least 6 cores.



In this session, you will perform tasks identical to what you did for the first one. You will respond to letters and read some texts.
Colours_1: Both male and female birds can have colourful feathers.
questionAndAnswerQuestion: According to the text, what is true about birds?
questionAndAnswerCorrectAnswer: Their visual perception of colours is well developed.
questionAndAnswerResponse: Both male and female birds can have colourful feathers.
questionAndAnswer01: Colours_1|Their visual perception of colours is well developed.|According to the text, what is true about birds?|Their visual perception of colours is well developed.|They can't distinguish between wasps and harmless flies.|Both male and female birds can have colourful feathers.|They are all attracted to bright colors.|They use camouflage as their primary defense.
questionAndAnswer02: Colours_2|To attract insects, which help them reproduce|What is the purpose of coloured flowers in plants?|To signal to other plants when it's time to bloom|To absorb more sunlight for photosynthesis|To attract insects, which help them reproduce|To warn predators that the plant is poisonous|To attract birds for pollination

This experiment session is a continuation of the previous session of the experiment "Letter and Reading". It requires a computer with at least 6 cores.



In this session, you will perform tasks identical to what you did for the first one. You will respond to letters and read some texts.
instructionForBlock:
In this block, you will again need to keep your cursor at the center of a moving black cross until a letter appears. The letter will appear away from the cross. You must recognize it by typing it on the keyboard. In some trials, the letter might be very small. Try anyway.

Click on PROCEED to continue.
instructionForResponse: What letter did you see?
instructionForStimulus: Keep the cursor at the center of the black cross until the letter appears.

This experiment session is a continuation of the previous session of the experiment "Letter and Reading". It requires a computer with at least 6 cores.



In this session, you will perform tasks identical to what you did for the first one. You will respond to letters and read some texts.
instructionForBlock:
In this block, you will again need to keep your cursor at the center of a moving black cross until a letter appears. The letter will appear away from the cross. You must recognize it by typing it on the keyboard. In some trials, the letter might be very small. Try anyway.

Click on PROCEED to continue.
instructionForResponse: What letter did you see?
instructionForStimulus: Keep the cursor at the center of the black cross until the letter appears.
